===Types of railways===
To select which type of railway to build, click and hold the railway build button in the main menu.
[[File:en/Manual/Openttd-rail1.png|none|frame|Choose rail type]]
* [[en/Manual/Base Set/Railways|Normal railways]] - Available in 1926 (temperate climate) or around 1945 (other climates). Only steam and [https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diesel locomotive Diesel] trains run on this railway.
* [[en/Manual/Base Set/Electrified railways]] - Available in 1965, when electric trains arrive. Electric trains will run '''only''' on this type of track, unless you disable Electric Railways in the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings]]. Steam and diesel trains can still run on this railway.
* [[en/Manual/Base Set/Monorail]] - Available in 1999. Only trains built in a monorail depot can run on this railway.
* [[en/Manual/Base Set/MagLev]] - Available in 2022. Only Mag-Lev trains can run on this railway.

Note that the availability dates are not set in stone, but are directly linked to the availability of a corresponding vehicle, which can vary some months due to randomness of vehicle introduction, or be completely different if you use any vehicle [[en/Manual/NewGRF]].

==Building trains==
To build/purchase a new [[en/Manual/Trains]] follow these steps:
*Place/build a train [[en/Manual/Depots]] and then click it. You will be presented with the depot window. 
*Click "Build new vehicles". A new window will pop up with a list of trains to purchase. 
*Select an engine and click "Buy vehicle" at the bottom of the window. The train will then appear in one of the slots in the depot window and a train window will pop up. 
*Add wagons to your engine in the same manner. Two wagons fit in one game world tile.


